  "prompt_text": "Reflect on a type of question where you know you tend to perform poorly. What makes it difficult?",
  "response_text": "Question Type: Open-ended questions that require me to generate creative or abstract solutions, especially when they are open-ended and lack specific constraints or guidelines.\n\nExplanation: These types of questions are difficult for me because they often require me to think outside the box, which is not my strong suit. I tend to excel in questions that have clear-cut answers or follow a logical sequence of steps. When it comes to creative or abstract thinking, I struggle with generating unique and innovative ideas, and I may not always be able to recognize the most effective or efficient solutions.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 7 (I can analyze the question and identify the problem, but may struggle with finding the most precise solution)\nV (Verbal Fluency): 6 (I may have difficulty expressing my thoughts and ideas in a coherent and concise manner)\nG (Goal Directedness): 6 (I can identify the goal of the question, but may struggle with finding the most direct path to achieving it)\nP (Pattern Recognition): 7 (I can recognize patterns, but may struggle with applying them in creative or abstract ways)\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 6 (I may have lower confidence in my ability to generate creative or abstract solutions)\nQ (Query Interpretation): 7 (I can usually understand the question, but may struggle with interpreting its underlying meaning or intent)\nC (Contextual Awareness): 7 (I can consider the context of the question, but may struggle with applying it to generate creative or abstract solutions)\nY (Affective Modeling): 7 (I can understand the emotional context of the question, but may struggle with generating creative or abstract solutions that take emotional factors into account)\nF (Flexibility): 5 (I may struggle with being flexible and open to different approaches to solving the problem)\nD (Depth of Processing): 6 (I can process the question to some extent, but may not always delve deeply into the question or consider multiple perspectives)\n---END RATINGS---",
